        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-06-02 14:13:09.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\n* keyspace was changed from \"titan\" to \"janusgraph\", but not applied to a configuration file. Is there an equivalent for titan.properties ? \n\n* asdctool/src/main/resources/scripts/titanSchemaCreation.sh file should be adjusted, using the new command.\n\n* When applying on an existing installation, the migration script should be pointed to the old keyspace. Can you explain how to configure it?\n\n* Is there any performance impact when working with existing titan keyspace (comparing to a new keyspace from scratch)?\n\nThanks",
        "patchset_number": 5
      },
      {
        "id": "bfcb93918ee11cfe734f5ab630008302d3e937bf",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 553,
          "name": "Shrikant Awachar",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "Shrikant.Awachar@amdocs.com",
          "username": "Shri4LF"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-06-03 11:59:14.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\n• Keyspace will change in next patch for both configuration file and titan.properties\n\n• titanSchemaCreation.sh - file will update it in next patch.\n\n• When applying on an existing installation, the migration script will execute on old keyspace only (i.e. sdctitan) after that I am going to provide one more script which will rename keyspace.\n\n• There is no performance difference. I got same experience on titan and janus keyspace for VFs, Services I have created.",
        "patchset_number": 5
      },
